(8, 'session', 'Introduction to NoSQL Database MongoDB', 'introduction-to-nosql-database-mongodb', NULL, NULL, '2024-05-23', '7:30 - 8:30 PM', 'Online', 'Mumbai', '<div style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 10pt;\"><font face=\"Arial, Verdana\" style=\"\">A <b style=\"\">NoSQL database like MongoDB</b> offers a flexible alternative to traditional relational databases. Unlike SQL databases that rely on fixed schemas and tables, NoSQL databases store data in dynamic, schema-less formats, typically using JSON-like documents or key-value pairs. This flexibility enables easier handling of unstructured or semi-structured data, making it ideal for applications requiring scalability and agility. NoSQL databases excel in distributed environments, supporting high-performance queries, horizontal scaling, and diverse data models, while often prioritizing availability and partition tolerance over strict consistency. Popular use cases include real-time analytics, content management systems, and applications requiring flexible data models or handling large volumes of data.</font></div><div style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 10pt;\"><font face=\"Arial, Verdana\"><br></font></div><div style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 10pt;\"><font face=\"Arial, Verdana\"><b>Day 1: Understanding MongoDB Basics</b></font></div><div style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 10pt;\"><ul><li><font face=\"Arial, Verdana\">Introduction to MongoDB:</font></li><li><font face=\"Arial, Verdana\">Overview of MongoDB and its advantages over relational databases.</font></li><li><font face=\"Arial, Verdana\">Explanation of document-oriented data model.</font></li><li><font face=\"Arial, Verdana\">Installation and Setup:</font></li><li><font face=\"Arial, Verdana\">Configuration and starting MongoDB server.</font></li><li><font face=\"Arial, Verdana\">Working with Collections and Documents:</font></li><li><font face=\"Arial, Verdana\">Explanation of MongoDB collections and documents.</font></li><li><fon